==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prima facie
<hw>Pri"ma fa"ci*e</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., from abl. of
<ets>primus</ets> first + abl. of <ets>facies</ets> appearance.]</ety>
<def>At first view; on the first appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Prima facie evidence</b></col><cd> (of a fact)
<fld>(Law)</fld>, evidence which is sufficient to establish the fact
unless rebutted.</cd> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primage</ent>⟦br⟧
